<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1205]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">
A male specimen was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[641,739,1034,1060]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Murayama, S." box="[779,983,1034,1061]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="32 - 35" refId="ref6107" refString="Murayama, S. (1995) Descriptions of 3 new species and 5 new races of Chinese butterflies from Yunnan Province. Nature &amp; Insects, 30 (14), 32 - 35 [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1995">Murayama (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, and the specimen was retrieved in 
<collectionCode box="[1376,1437,1035,1061]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/pcbg-hhf5" name="Lake Biwa Museum" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">LBM</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,296,1070,1097]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[172,1425,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1425,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19–36. 19–21. Apostictopterus fulginosus jiangxiensis Murayama, 1983, holotype; 22–24. Aeromachus inachus jiujiangana Murayama, 1983, holotype; 25–27. Pedesta masuriensis cuneomaculata Murayama, 1995, holotype; 28–30. Thoressa dianchiana Murayama, 1995, holotype; 31–33. Thoressa nanshaona Murayama, 1995, holotype; 34–36. Lobocla bifasciata disparalis Murayama, 1995, holotype. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3990961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3990961/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Figs. 31–33</figureCitation>
; Dried Insect Database Reg. no. 1500022026).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1205]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, H. &amp; Zhan, C." box="[199,445,1106,1133]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="179 - 186" refId="ref5511" refString="Huang, H. &amp; Zhan, C. (2004) Notes on the genera Thoressa and Pedesta, with description of a new species from South China. Neue Entomologische Nachrichten, 57, 179 - 186." type="journal article" year="2004">Huang &amp; Zhan (2004)</bibRefCitation>
examined the 
<typeStatus box="[606,654,1107,1133]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">type</typeStatus>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, H." box="[706,860,1107,1133]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="193 - 200" refId="ref5475" refString="Huang, H. (2011) Notes on the genus Thoressa Swinhoe, [1913] from China, with the description of a new species. Atalanta, 42, 193 - 200." type="journal article" year="2011">Huang (2011)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murayama" authorityYear="1995" box="[948,1071,1106,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanshaona">
<emphasis box="[948,1071,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">nanshaona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Niceville, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="de Niceville" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Thoressa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Thoressa pandita</emphasis>
(de Nicéville, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
. We follow his treatment. Again, we retain the conventional view and consider 
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">panditia</emphasis>
a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hemming" authorityYear="1934" box="[289,378,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,378,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Pedesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
